node.text:
The Honda Rider Education Centers are the perfect places to introduced new riders to powersports in a safe environment and with trained instructors. In this video, we joined four riders as they tried their hands at off-road motorcycling with the CRF Trail family of dirt bikes, at the Colton, California, HREC campus. There are similar facilities in Alpharetta, Georgia; Irving, Texas; and Troy, Ohio. Classes are also offered on street riding, ATV riding and side-by-side driving.

https://powersports.honda.com/rider-education

Please note that this video was shot prior to the COVID-19 pandemic. Appropriate safety measures are currently being followed.

node.title: Learning to Ride CRF Trail Bikes at the Honda Rider Education Center

A group of journalists recently had the opportunity to try the new model in and around Julian, California.

node.text: Honda’s new 2021 Rebel 1100 is going to change the way you think about cruisers. Sure, it has the low seat height, twin-cylinder engine and relaxed riding position that make cruiser-class machines so timelessly popular. But it also has something most cruisers lack: genuine arm-straightening performance, and a chassis and suspension that let you dial up the pace when the road gets twisty. Plus, since the Rebel 1100 out performs just about any cruiser, we didn’t fall into the trap of just making it look like grandpa’s sled either.  You can choose between our revolutionary automatic DCT transmission or a conventional six-speed manual. Ride it one the weekends. Ride it at night. On the boulevard or in the canyons. Dress it up or dress it down with our extensive line of Honda accessories. The new Rebel 1100 can do it all—and you’ll have a blast doing it. #rebel1100 #bornrebel #betteronahonda

node.text: In racing, series finales are always unique, marking a transition between seasons. Team Honda HRC closed the 2020 season on a high note at the last AMA Pro Motocross round, with Chase Sexton earning his first overall win in the 450 class. Even before the champagne dried, the team was already thinking ahead to preparing the 2021 Honda CRF450R for Sexton and Ken Roczen for the 2021 season.

node.text: For 2022, this bona fide closed-course off-road weapon is all-new, with the same upgrades as the motocross-focused CRF250R. Those changes, which result in reduced weight, more low-end power and improved durability, are particularly well-suited to closed-course off-road series such as NGPC, GNCC and WORCS—the realms of top teams like SLR Honda, JCR Honda and Phoenix Racing Honda. Making the bike even better suited for those applications, the CRF250RX comes standard with model-specific features such as a resin 2.1-gallon fuel tank, dedicated suspension and ECU settings, an 18-inch rear wheel and plastic hand guards. #crf250rx

Announcing the 2022 CRF250R motocrosser! Completely redesigned, the motocross machine is ready for Jett and Hunter Lawrence, featuring a host of updates that make handling more agile, improve acceleration on corner exits, and increase endurance over race distance. The engine produces more low-rpm torque while retaining strong top-end power, for a broader powerband. Chassis updates delivered significant weight savings and better ergonomics to improve the model’s already-excellent handling prowess. A redesigned exhaust system and additional lightened components resulted in a substantial reduction of 8 pounds. In addition, durability was improved through thorough reexamination of the engine, its cooling system and the drive components, while notable improvements were also made to the clutch.
#crf250r #2022crf250r

For more info, visit link in bio.

In this #ConnectedByRiding post, celebrating our diverse Powersport Community and love of riding, we get to know Donald Frye, a member of the @redrummc on his custom 2015 Stateline VT1300CR. The Red Rum M.C. is for indigenous motorcycle enthusiasts. 

Where do you live?:
Hesperia, CA

What do you ride?:
2015 Honda Stateline VT1300CR

Favorite part of the powersports community?:
When it comes to Honda motorcycles you get a lot of bike for your money and dependability that no one can beat.

What would you like to see more of in the Powersport community?:
I would like see more aftermarket accessories, different rims, handlebars, luggage racks, fairings and engine upgrades like intakes, exhaust and ignition.

Anything else to add?:
I'm part of the Redrum M.C. Mojave River Cali chapter.
